Crotalaria brevides var. brevides

    Authority   Benth.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
     Synonyms
   Common names Ethiopian rattlebox (English)
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4967

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A fast growing erect or decumbent herb with trifoliate leaves and pale
   yellow flowers. The plant reaches 0.5-2.0 m in height
   GROWING PERIOD
   Annual or short-lived perennial herb.
   COMMON NAMES
   Slenderleaf crotalaria.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms: C. intermedia, C. purpureo-lineata. Slenderleaf
   crotalaria can be found in northern Africa. In the tropics it is most
   common in grassy or light wooded areas at altitudes between 600-2700 m.
   The plant that require little attention. Yields of about 2-3.5 t/ha
   have been reported. Unlike other crotalarias, slenderleaf crotolaria is
   considered nontoxin.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 179 [USE, TEXT, LIG]
   Duke J 1981 pp 61-63 317 [DRA, FER, TEXT, RAIN, TEMP, PH]
   Purseglove J 1974 pp 250 [USE]
   Bogdan A 1977 pp 337 [DRA, USE]

